TITLE: Defining Employee Data Structure in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This JSON structure defines an array of employee objects, each containing personal, HR, and contact information. The data includes names, positions, salaries, start dates, and location details for various employees.
SOURCE: https://github.com/datatables/datatables/blob/master/examples/ajax/data/objects_deep.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JSON
CODE:
```
{
    "name": "Donna Snider",
    "hr": {
        "position": "Customer Support",
        "salary": "$112,000",
        "start_date": "2011\/01\/25"
    },
    "contact": [
        "New York",
        "4226"
    ]
}
```

